# Testing (deterministic XCUITest, two tiers)

Tests are run by `scripts/*.sh` + `xcodebuild`, **never** by an agent driving the screen
(the old computer-use / desktop-MCP harness is gone). Keep tests deterministic and
self-driving. See [`AGENTS.md`](mdc:AGENTS.md) §12 and the testing runbook.

## Two tiers (iOS)

- **Tier A — fake backend** (`QVOICE_FAKE_ENGINE=1`): smoke, sheets, and the Studio
  backend-state flow (generate → inline player, error surface). Driven by
  [`FakeTTSEngine`](mdc:Sources/iOS/FakeTTSEngine.swift) + `FakeModelStatusProvider` — no
  2.3 GB model, no Metal. The shared coordinator
  [`VocelloUITestApp`](mdc:Tests/VocelloiOSUITests/VocelloUITestApp.swift) always launches
  this. **Runs on the iOS Simulator and in CI**, and on device. This is the fast pre-merge
  signal.
- **Tier B — real engine** (cold generation, real download): needs the in-process MLX
  engine on a **paired physical iPhone**. These suites self-launch their own app (no fake
  flag) and are guarded with `XCTSkipUnless(UITestTier.canRunRealEngine, …)`.

`UITestTier.canRunRealEngine` is a **compile-time** gate (`#if targetEnvironment(simulator)`):
false on the Simulator, true on device. No runner-env flag is needed — `scripts/ios_device.sh`
selects which suites run on device (`--cold` for cold generation), and CI runs only the
Tier-A suites on the Simulator via `-only-testing`.

## Determinism rules

- Use `waitForExistence` / `XCTNSPredicateExpectation`, **not** `usleep`/`Thread.sleep`/
  RunLoop polling, to wait for UI.
- Register `installSystemAlertMonitor()` in `setUp` so permission/automation dialogs can't
  stall a run.
- Query by stable `accessibilityIdentifier`; do not rely on brittle label/hierarchy
  fallbacks. Never let a `screen_*` container shadow descendant ids — use the
  `screenPresenceMarker(_:)` leaf marker (see [`IOSAccessibility`](mdc:Sources/iOS/IOSAccessibility.swift)).

## Real-engine work is on-device only

The iOS Simulator cannot host the MLX/Metal engine, so real model load / generation /
download is validated on a paired iPhone via `scripts/ios_device.sh`. The Simulator is
allowed **only** for Tier-A fake-backend tests. macOS UI smoke runs via
`scripts/macos_test.sh test` (calls `models ensure` first; exports
`QVOICE_REQUIRE_TEST_MODELS=1` so missing weights fail instead of `XCTSkip`).

## Model preflight (macOS)

- Canonical weights: `~/Library/Application Support/QwenVoice/models`.
- Debug/test context symlinks `QwenVoice-Debug/models` → canonical
  ([`scripts/lib/test_models.sh`](mdc:scripts/lib/test_models.sh)).
- `scripts/macos_test.sh models check|ensure|install` — see testing runbook §1b.
- Escape: `QVOICE_SKIP_MODEL_ENSURE=1`, `QVOICE_TEST_MODELS_NO_NETWORK=1`.
